The Department of Corrections shall consist of the following organizational units:
Personnel Division;
Office of Adult Institutions, which shall have the following divisions:
Division of Operations and Program Services;
Division of Medical Services;
Division of Mental Health Services;
Division of Substance Abuse Programming;
Division of Correctional Industries;
Division of Kentucky State Reformatory;
Division of Luther Luckett Correctional Complex;
Division of Roederer Correctional Complex;
Division of Blackburn Correctional Complex;
Division of Kentucky Correctional Institution for Women;
Division of Northpoint Training Center Division;
Division of Eastern Kentucky Correctional Complex;
Division of Bell County Forestry Camp;
Division of Kentucky State Penitentiary;
Division of Western Kentucky Correctional Complex;
Division of Green River Correctional Complex; and
Division of Little Sandy Correctional Complex. Each division specified in paragraphs (f) to (q) of this subsection shall be headed by a warden pursuant to KRS 196.160;
Office of Community Services and Facilities, which shall have the following divisions:
Division of Probation and Parole; and
Division of Local Facilities; and
Office of Support Services, which shall have the following divisions:
Division of Administrative Services;
Division of Corrections Training;
Division of Population Management; and
Division of Parole and Victim Services.
